{"title_page": "Crystal Mountain (Michigan)", "text_new": "{{about|the ski area in Michigan||Crystal Mountain (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox ski area\n|name=Crystal Mountain\n|logo=CMLogo200.png\n|location= [[Thompsonville, Michigan|Thompsonville]],<br>[[Weldon Township, Michigan]]\n|vertical=375 ft.\n|top_elevation= {{convert|1132|ft|m|abbr=on}}.\n|base_elevation= {{convert|757|ft|m|abbr=on}}.\n|skiable_area= {{convert|103|acre|m2}}\n|number_trails=58\n|nightskiing=27 slopes lighted for night skiing, five nights a week (early and late season varies)\n|longest_run= One half mile\n|liftsystem=9 total: 1 detachable high-speed quad chair, 3 fixed-grip quad chairs, 2 triple chairs, 1 double chair, and 2 \"carpet style\" surface lifts\n|lift_capacity= 12,400 skiers per hour\n|terrainparks=4\n|snowfall=132\" average per year\n|snowmaking=98%\n|external_link={{url|http://www.crystalmountain.com}}\n}}\n[[Image:Crystal Mountain - Cheers Chair.jpg|thumb|300px|View of the \"''Cheers''\" chair lift and resort from near one of the peaks. Thompsonville air strip (7Y2) visible in the background]]\n'''Crystal Mountain Resort''' is a [[resort]] and [[conference center]] located in [[Weldon Township, Michigan|Weldon Township]], [[Benzie County]], [[Michigan]], just west of [[Thompsonville, Michigan|Thompsonville]]. The resort's area forms the [[Crystal Mountain, Michigan|Crystal Mountain]] [[census-designated place]]. The resort offers recreational activities including [[Downhill skiing|downhill]] and [[cross country skiing]] the winter months, and golf, water activities, and an [[alpine slide]] in other seasons. The resort was founded in 1956.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skiinghistory.org/history/ski-resorts-years-they-were-founded|title=Ski Resorts: Years They Were Founded - International Skiing History Association|publisher=|accessdate=21 June 2016}}</ref> In March 2015 the resort announced it was planning a $9 million expansion project that will add new ski runs, lifts, lodging, retail and other amenities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mlive.com/business/west-michigan/index.ssf/2015/03/crystal_mountain_expansion.html|title=$9M Crystal Mountain expansion will add 'Backyard' ski slopes, lodging, retail|work=MLive.com|accessdate=29 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Skiing and snowboarding==\nThe resort's skiing and snowboarding season runs from approximately Thanksgiving weekend to early April, depending on weather conditions. The resort receives an average of 11' of natural snowfall, however [[artificial snow]] can be made when natural snowfall is lacking.  The resort has 58 downhill slopes, 6 [[chairlift]]s and 2 surface lifts, with 27 slopes lighted for night skiing during the peak ski season. It is also home to Jim Riley-Lampinen ranked number 1 boot fit in Michigan.\n\n==Golf==\nCrystal Mountain features two 18-hole championship golf courses. The Betsie Valley course, the resort's original golf course, plays at {{convert|6567|yd}} from the blue tees. The Mountain Ridge course, which hosts the Michigan Women's Open each summer, plays {{convert|7077|yd}} from the blue tees.\n\nThe resort's golf school offers golf instruction to players of all ages and ability levels.\n\n== Recreational facilities ==\nCrystal Mountain maintains Michigan's only [[Alpine slide]].  The resort also maintains mountain biking trails available during the Summer.\n\n==Lodging==\nOvernight lodging is available in over 250 hotel rooms, suites, condominiums, townhouses and vacation homes, which are located near the skiing and golf facilities throughout the resort property.\n\n==Awards and recognition==\nCrystal Mountain is one of 60 golf courses in Michigan to be certified by the Michigan Turfgrass Environmental Stewardship Program. Its golf school has been named a Top 25 golf school by ''[[Golf Magazine]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.golf.com/instruction/list-top-25-golf-schools-america?page=2|title=The List:Top 25 Golf Schools|publisher=[[Golf Magazine]]|date=8 October 2008|accessdate=30 August 2014}}</ref> Crystal Mountain was named among Conde Nast Traveler's Ten Best Family Ski Resorts in the U.S. and Canada in 2017, and also ranked the resort #1 in the United States for Family Reunions in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.michiganpgagolf.com/teacher/|title=Teacher Of The Year|publisher=[[Professional Golfers Association]], Michigan Section|accessdate=30 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.freep.com/story/sports/outdoors/2016/01/13/michigan-ski-resorts/78768322/|title=Michigan\u2019s ski resorts back up and running|date=13 January 2016|work=Detroit Free Press|accessdate=29 January 2016}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.9and10news.com/story/30956801/sightseeing-in-northern-michigan-crystal-mountain-skier-services|title=Sightseeing in Northern Michigan: Crystal Mountain Skier Service|author=Adkins, Corey|date=13 January 2016|publisher=|accessdate=29 January 2016}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/12/29/crystal-mountain-resort-ski-guide_n_1174766.html|title=Crystal Mountain Resort and Spa: A Huffington Post Travel Ski Resort Guide|date=30 December 2011|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=29 January 2016}}\n* {{cite web|url=https://www.cntraveler.com/galleries/2014-12-03/tahoe-sun-valley-mont-tremblant-top-10-family-friendly-ski-resorts-in-north-america|title=The Best Family Ski Resorts in the U.S. and Canada|date=20 January 2017|publisher=|accessdate=6 June 2018}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.crystalmountain.com/ Official website]\n\n{{Mountains of Michigan}}\n\n{{coord|44|31|12|N|85|59|32|W|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Benzie County, Michigan]]\n[[Category:Ski areas and resorts in Michigan]]\n[[Category:Sports venues in Michigan]]\n[[Category:Mountains of Michigan]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Benzie County, Michigan]]\n[[Category:Landforms of Benzie County, Michigan]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the ski area in Michigan||Crystal Mountain (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox ski area\n|name=Crystal Mountain\n|logo=CMLogo200.png\n|location= [[Thompsonville, Michigan|Thompsonville]],<br>[[Weldon Township, Michigan]]\n|vertical=375 ft.\n|top_elevation= {{convert|1132|ft|m|abbr=on}}.\n|base_elevation= {{convert|757|ft|m|abbr=on}}.\n|skiable_area= {{convert|103|acre|m2}}\n|number_trails=58\n|nightskiing=27 slopes lighted for night skiing, five nights a week (early and late season varies)\n|longest_run= One half mile\n|liftsystem=9 total: 1 detachable high-speed quad chair, 3 fixed-grip quad chairs, 2 triple chairs, 1 double chair, and 2 \"carpet style\" surface lifts\n|lift_capacity= 12,400 skiers per hour\n|terrainparks=4\n|snowfall=132\" average per year\n|snowmaking=98%\n|external_link={{url|http://www.crystalmountain.com}}\n}}\n[[Image:Crystal Mountain - Cheers Chair.jpg|thumb|300px|View of the \"''Cheers''\" chair lift and resort from near one of the peaks. Thompsonville air strip (7Y2) visible in the background]]\n'''Crystal Mountain Resort''' is a [[resort]] and [[conference center]] located in [[Weldon Township, Michigan|Weldon Township]], [[Benzie County]], [[Michigan]], just west of [[Thompsonville, Michigan|Thompsonville]]. The resort's area forms the [[Crystal Mountain, Michigan|Crystal Mountain]] [[census-designated place]]. The resort offers recreational activities including [[Downhill skiing|downhill]] and [[cross country skiing]] the winter months, and golf, water activities, and an [[alpine slide]] in other seasons. The resort was founded in 1956.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.skiinghistory.org/history/ski-resorts-years-they-were-founded|title=Ski Resorts: Years They Were Founded - International Skiing History Association|publisher=|accessdate=21 June 2016}}</ref> In March 2015 the resort announced it was planning a $9 million expansion project that will add new ski runs, lifts, lodging, retail and other amenities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mlive.com/business/west-michigan/index.ssf/2015/03/crystal_mountain_expansion.html|title=$9M Crystal Mountain expansion will add 'Backyard' ski slopes, lodging, retail|work=MLive.com|accessdate=29 January 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Skiing and snowboarding==\nThe resort's skiing and snowboarding season runs from approximately Thanksgiving weekend to early April, depending on weather conditions. The resort receives an average of 11' of natural snowfall, however [[artificial snow]] can be made when natural snowfall is lacking.  The resort has 58 downhill slopes, 6 [[chairlift]]s and 2 surface lifts, with 27 slopes lighted for night skiing during the peak ski season. It is also home to Jim Riley-Lampinen ranked number 1 boot fit in Michigan.\n\n==Golf==\nCrystal Mountain features two 18-hole championship golf courses. The Betsie Valley course, the resort's original golf course, plays at {{convert|6567|yd}} from the blue tees. The Mountain Ridge course, which hosts the Michigan Women's Open each summer, plays {{convert|7077|yd}} from the blue tees.\n\nThe resort's golf school offers golf instruction to players of all ages and ability levels.\n\n== Recreational facilities ==\nCrystal Mountain maintains Michigan's only [[Alpine slide]].  The resort also maintains mountain biking trails available during the Summer.\n\n==Lodging==\nOvernight lodging is available in over 250 hotel rooms, suites, condominiums, townhouses and vacation homes, which are located near the skiing and golf facilities throughout the resort property.\n\n==Awards and recognition==\nCrystal Mountain is one of 60 golf courses in Michigan to be certified by the Michigan Turfgrass Environmental Stewardship Program. Its golf school has been named a Top 25 golf school by ''[[Golf Magazine]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.golf.com/instruction/list-top-25-golf-schools-america?page=2|title=The List:Top 25 Golf Schools|publisher=[[Golf Magazine]]|date=8 October 2008|accessdate=30 August 2014}}</ref> Crystal Mountain was named among Conde Nast Traveler\u2019s Ten Best Family Ski Resorts in the U.S. and Canada in 2017, and also ranked the resort #1 in the United States for Family Reunions in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.michiganpgagolf.com/teacher/|title=Teacher Of The Year|publisher=[[Professional Golfers Association]], Michigan Section|accessdate=30 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.freep.com/story/sports/outdoors/2016/01/13/michigan-ski-resorts/78768322/|title=Michigan\u2019s ski resorts back up and running|date=13 January 2016|work=Detroit Free Press|accessdate=29 January 2016}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.9and10news.com/story/30956801/sightseeing-in-northern-michigan-crystal-mountain-skier-services|title=Sightseeing in Northern Michigan: Crystal Mountain Skier Service|author=Adkins, Corey|date=13 January 2016|publisher=|accessdate=29 January 2016}}\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/12/29/crystal-mountain-resort-ski-guide_n_1174766.html|title=Crystal Mountain Resort and Spa: A Huffington Post Travel Ski Resort Guide|date=30 December 2011|work=The Huffington Post|accessdate=29 January 2016}}\n* {{cite web|url=https://www.cntraveler.com/galleries/2014-12-03/tahoe-sun-valley-mont-tremblant-top-10-family-friendly-ski-resorts-in-north-america|title=The Best Family Ski Resorts in the U.S. and Canada|date=20 January 2017|publisher=|accessdate=6 June 2018}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.crystalmountain.com/ Official website]\n\n{{Mountains of Michigan}}\n\n{{coord|44|31|12|N|85|59|32|W|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Benzie County, Michigan]]\n[[Category:Ski areas and resorts in Michigan]]\n[[Category:Sports venues in Michigan]]\n[[Category:Mountains of Michigan]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Benzie County, Michigan]]\n[[Category:Landforms of Benzie County, Michigan]]\n", "name_user": "Amkgp", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eAwards and recognition:clean up,typo