{"title_page": "Chigusa Kitani", "text_new": "{{Infobox artist\n| honorific_prefix = \n| name             = {{nihongo|Chigusa Kitani|\u6728\u8c37 \u5343\u7a2e|Kitani Chigusa}}\n| honorific_suffix = \n| image            = Kitani Chigusa.jpg\n| image_size       = 200px\n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| native_name      = \n| native_name_lang = \n| birth_name       = {{nihongo|Ei Yoshioka|\u5409\u5ca1 \u82f1|Yoshioka Ei}}\n| birth_date       = {{Birth date|1895|02|17}}\n| birth_place      = {{JPN}}, [[Kita-ku, Osaka]], [[Osaka Prefecture]]\n| death_date       = {{death date and age|1947|01|24|1895|02|17|mf=yes}}\n| death_place      = [[Minamikawachi District, Osaka|Minamikawachi District]], [[Osaka|Osaka Prefecture]]\n| resting_place    = \n| resting_place_coordinates = <!-- {{Coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| nationality      = {{JPN}}\n| residence        = \n| education        = [[Shimizudani High School|Shimizudani Girls' High School]]\n| alma_mater       = \n| known_for        = [[Japanese painting|Painting]]\n| notable_works    = \n| style            = {{nihongo|[[Bijin-ga]]|\u7f8e\u4eba\u753b||\"beautiful person picture\"}}\n| home_town        = \n| movement         = {{nihongo|[[Nihonga]]|\u65e5\u672c\u753b}}\n| spouse           = \n| partner          = \n| awards           = <!-- {{awd|award|year|title|role|name}} (optional) -->\n| elected          = \n| patrons          = \n| memorials        = \n| website          = <!-- {{URL|Example.com}} -->\n| module           = \n}}\n{{nihongo|'''Chigusa Kitani'''|\u6728\u8c37 \u5343\u7a2e|Kitani Chigusa|February 17, 1895 - January 24, 1947}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.city.osaka.lg.jp/contents/wdu120/artrip/en/gallery_07.html|title=KITANI (YOSHIOKA) Chigusa\u00abOngoku\u00bb\uff5cOur Collection\uff5cArtrip Museum : Osaka City Museum of Modern Art|website=www.city.osaka.lg.jp}}</ref> was a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] {{nihongo|[[Nihonga]]|\u65e5\u672c\u753b}} [[Painting|painter]] and painting teacher in [[Taish\u014d period|Taish\u014d]] and [[Sh\u014dwa period|Sh\u014dwa]] [[Japan]].\n\n== Life ==\n[[Art name|Born]] Chigusa Kitani at [[Kita-ku, Osaka]] {{nihongo|D\u014djima|[[:ja:\u5802\u5cf6]]}}, the center of the [[Osaka]] (the second largest [[Metropolitan area|metropolitan]] area in [[Japan]]), in 1895 under the name {{nihongo|Ei Yoshioka|\u5409\u5ca1 \u82f1|Yoshioka Ei}}.\n\nWhile studying at [[Shimizudani High School|Shimizudani Girls' High School]], She studied [[Bird-and-flower painting]] under {{nihongo|Chokuj\u014d Fukada|[[:ja:\u6df1\u7530\u76f4\u57ce]]|Fukada Chokuj\u014d}} who is a famous painter of the {{nihongo|[[Shij\u014d school]]|\u56db\u6761\u6d3e|Shij\u014d-ha}}.<ref> also known as the ''Maruyama\u2013Shij\u014d'' school</ref> She moved to [[Tokyo]] in 1913 ([[Taish\u014d]] 2) to study under {{nihongo|Sh\u014den Ikeda|[[:ja:\u6c60\u7530\u8549\u5712]]|Ikeda Sh\u014den}}.\n[[File:Frontispiece by Kitani Chigusa 03.jpg|left|thumb|{{nihongo|[[Kuchi-e]]|\u53e3\u7d75|[[Book frontispiece|frontispieces]] of books}} - [[Lithography]]]]\nAfter returning to Osaka, She became a pupil of {{nihongo|Tsunetomi Kitano|[[:ja:\u5317\u91ce\u6052\u5bcc]]|Kitano Tsunetomi}} and {{nihongo|Kyuho Noda|[[:ja:\u91ce\u7530\u4e5d\u6d66]]|Noda Kyuho}}. Kitano is famous painter who draws ({{nihongo|[[Bijin-ga]]|\u7f8e\u4eba\u753b||\"beautiful person picture\", is a generic term for pictures of beautiful women in [[Japanese art]]}} .<ref>* [http://www.nak-osaka.jp/en/gallery_07.html KITANI (YOSHIOKA) Chigusa&#171;Ongoku&#187;\uff5cOur Collection\uff5cArtrip Museum : Nakanoshima Museum of Art, Osaka]. Retrieved 2020-04-18.</ref>\n[[File:Hari-kuy\u014d by Kitani Chigusa from the picture post card.jpg|right|thumb|250px|{{nihongo|[[Hari-Kuy\u014d]]|\u91dd\u4f9b\u990a| (Memorial ceremony Festival of Broken Needles) - Postcard}}]]\n\nIn 1919, She started studying under {{nihongo|Keigetsu Kikuchi|[[:ja:\u83ca\u6c60\u5951\u6708]]|Kikuchi Keigetsu}} in Kyoto. \n\nShe trained in [[Seattle]], [[Washington (state)|Washington]], in the [[United States]] for two years from the age of 13, and her work was exhibited throughout Japan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kagedo.com/wordpress/g/kitani-chigusa-painting-of-a-beauty-contemplating-her-reflection/ |title=Kagedo Japanese Art Kitani Chigusa, Painting of a Beauty Contemplating her Reflection - Kagedo Japanese Art |publisher=Kagedo.com |date= |accessdate=2018-06-05}}</ref>\n\nIn 1920, She married {{nihongo|H\u014dgin Kitani||[[:ja:\u6728\u8c37\u84ec\u541f]]|Kitani H\u014dgin}}, a researcher on [[Chikamatsu Monzaemon]] ([[drama|dramatist]] of [[J\u014druri (music)|j\u014druri]]). In the same year, She established a painting school {{nihongo|Yachigusa-kai|\u516b\u5343\u8349\u4f1a}} and {{nihongo|Chigusa-kai|\u5343\u7a2e\u4f1a}} at her home in Osaka. She aimed to nurture, instruct and improve the status of female painters.\n[[File:The_painting_\"Mayu_no_nagori\"_with_Kitani_Chigusa.jpg|left|thumb|With her painting {{nihongo|Mayu no Nagori|\u7709\u306e\u540d\u6b8b|Care for and Remnants the eyebrows}}]]\nShe died in 1947 ([[Sh\u014dwa (1926\u20131989)|Sh\u014dwa]] 22) in the [[Minamikawachi District, Osaka|Minamikawachi]] of Osaka at the age of 51.\n\n== Works ==\nIn 1915, Chigusa Kitani was 20years old, was selected for the 1st {{nihongo|Osaka Fine Arts Exhibition|\u5927\u962a\u7f8e\u8853\u5c55\u89a7\u4f1a|Osaka Bijutu Tenrankai}} as {{nihongo|''Shin-kyo''|\u65b0\u5c45|\"New house\"}} and for the 9th {{nihongo|Ministry of Education Art Fine Arts Exhibition|\u6587\u90e8\u7701\u7f8e\u8853\u5c55\u89a7\u4f1a (\u6587\u5c55,[[Bunten]])|Monbu-Sho Bijutu Tenrankai}}<ref>It was renamed the {{nihongo|Imperial Fine Arts Academy Exhibition|\u5e1d\u56fd\u7f8e\u8853\u9662\u5c55\u89a7\u4f1a (\u5e1d\u5c55,[[Teiten]])|Teikoku Bijutu-in Tenrankai}} in 1911.</ref> as {{nihongo|''[[Hari-Kuy\u014d]]''|\u91dd\u4f9b\u990a|\"Memorial ceremony Festival of Broken Needles\"}}.This Hari-Kuy\u014d is a work depicting a [[Geisha]] girl in Kyoto.\n\nShe showed her works at the exhibitions such as {{nihongo|Imperial Fine Arts Academy Exhibition|\u5e1d\u56fd\u7f8e\u8853\u9662\u5c55\u89a7\u4f1a (\u5e1d\u5c55,[[Teiten]])|Teikoku Bijutu-in Tenrankai}}, {{nihongo|Kikuchijuku-ten|\u83ca\u6c60\u587e\u5c55|\"Exhibition for private school by Keigetsu Kikuchi\"}} and Yachigusakai-ten (Yachigusakai's Exhibition).\n\n=== Gallery ===\n<gallery widths=\"230\" heights=\"230\">\nFile:Mayu no nagori by Kitani Chigusa.jpg|{{nihongo|Mayu no Nagori|\u7709\u306e\u540d\u6b8b|Care for and Remnants the eyebrows|1925}}\nFile:Ongoku by Kitani Chigusa (Osaka City Museum of Modern Art).jpg|{{nihongo|Ongoku|\u3092\u3093\u3054\u304f|Distant country |1918}}\nFile:Shinj\u016b yoig\u014dshin no O-chiyo by Kitani Chigusa.jpg|{{nihongo|Shinju Yoi Goshin no Ochiyo|[[:ja:\u5fc3\u4e2d\u7269|\u5fc3\u4e2d\u5bb5\u5e9a\u7533]]\u3001\u304a\u5343\u4ee3|Ochiyo at \"double love suicide\"|1922|[[Woodcut]]}} from \"Complete works of [[Chikamatsu Monzaemon]]\" by H\u014dgin Kitani\nFile:Joruri Boat by Kitani Chigusa.jpg|{{nihongo|[[J\u014druri (music)|J\u014druri]] Bune|\u6d44\u7460\u7483\u8239|Small boat for playing J\u014druri music|1926}}\nFile:Frontispiece by Kitani Chigusa 01.jpg|{{nihongo|[[Kuchi-e]]|\u53e3\u7d75|[[Book frontispiece|frontispieces]] of books}} - [[Lithography]]\nFile:Frontispiece by Kitani Chigusa 02.jpg|Kuchi-e (Lithography)\n</gallery>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{commonscat}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6ZjqDb-zwVQC&lpg=PA68&dq=KITANI%20Chigusa&pg=PA78#v=onepage&q=KoTANI%20Chigusa&f=false|title=Guide to Modern Japanese Woodblock Prints: 1900-1975|last=Merritt|first=Helen|last2=Yamada|first2=Nanako|date=1995|publisher=University of Hawaii Press|year=|isbn=9780824817329|location=|page=78}}\n*{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iQ7rAAAAMAAJ&q=KITANI+Chigusa&dq=KITANI+Chigusa&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi1mOqfxL3bAhUpIDQIHb_dAcQQ6AEIPTAE|title=\u30